Ukraine’s Sovereign Debt Increased 3.1% in April, Ministry Says

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-06-07T09:35:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/ukraine-s-sovereign-debt-increased-3-1-in-april-ministry-says.html
Ukraine’s state debt, including
guarantees, rose 3.1 percent in April as the government
increased domestic borrowing, the  Finance Ministry  said.  Sovereign debt increased to $58.17 billion as of April 30
from $56.42 billion a month earlier, the ministry said today in
a  statement  from the capital, Kiev.  Domestic debt rose to $19.22 billion from $18.56 billion at
the end of March, the ministry said. Obligations to foreign
creditors climbed to $24.33 billion from $24.06 billion,
according to the statement.  Ukraine’s state debt rose 7.1 percent in the first four
months of 2011 as the government sold Eurobonds and domestic
bonds to cover the  budget deficit . The government also increased
the capital of state energy company NAK Naftogaz Ukrainy by 5
billion hryvnia ($626 million) and injected 3.9 billion hryvnia
into state-owned PAT Rodovid Bank, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
